column5: Nice batch.  WHen's dinner i'll bring the Fish Crisp.  Great Pics.
hmm good haul, wishin i was able to join in on the feeding frenzy; crappie goood
Should be enough dinner there for yourself, what about the wife.  Nice report.
Great haul G.  Mmmmmmm.  At least those damned suspended fish were cooperating  Joey

Thanks Glen seeing fish keeps us happy since were not sure what kind of fishing we will be doing in January.After 2 weekends of fishing(Skunked) I can't wait to post some fish not just nice scenery.Bon appetit.Enjoy the meal.Mike
Thanks for the fishing report, Glen....and the biology lesson...and the history lesson   and the geography lesson. I'm amazed that you know about yellow bass.  Congrats on the great day, Bubba.
Nice catch Glen......  I always liked history,even in schooll....thanx for the interesting thread....   Cheers !!
GLEN,nice mess of fish you redneck    wtg.what was the size of that Crappie,they are so tasty.  Steve
Nice pics GCD and nice haul.
Must be nice, a little frost to start the day, then shirtsleeves in the PM. Nice catch, betcha they taste great!

Geez, no dam pics, kinda looks wierd to see a report from you without concrete on either your left or right side, lol.   Just kiddin Glen, nice catch there, and I am sure they are going to taste great for the next couple of days. Took me 3 days to eat my two fish from last saturday.
nice catch glen,looks like a real nice fish fry tonight   what time should myself and my fishergirl come over,ill bring the fish-crisp   nice report & pics       cheers

Looks like a good day of catching, you're lucky to be able to get out on the boat this late in the year.  Though with the mild temps we've been having in southern Ontario, we've been getting some local boat reports too!  Mike
